   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>27.7.1882 Donnerstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName>. July 27. 1882</p>
            <p> I received about the worst news I could have received today. The Head<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="667">Sneyd-Kynnersley</persName>
               </note> has received a letter from <persName key="176">Papa</persName> saying that I
               must leave this school this term and go to some Gymnasium or something like it in
                  <placeName key="50613">Baden</placeName>. I wish I could stop here for at least
               another term, or any time, because I can by no means relish the prospect before me. I
               am very sorry at having to leave this place. We had a dress rehearsal tonight. It
               went off pretty well, all but the last scene, which we do not know properly and which
               does not end up the piece nicely. So we are going to get some redlights, and are
               going to act the part where Strepsiades sets the house on fire.</p>
         </div>
